			<summary>
				<narrativeincludeclinical>The patient took the product on Wednesday, 07/30/14. Her doctor instructed her to take 2 dulcolax tablets at 4pm. She then took her first dose at 6pm with the required water. At 10:45 she got concerned that she was not having a bowel movement so she (on her own-not doctor's instructed) took two more dulcolax tablets. At 11:30 pm she did start having multiple small bowel movements. The patient describes them to be the consistency and color of honey. At 8am the next morning (07/31/14) she took the second dose. She then laid down in bed to rest before she had to go in for her colonoscopy. She had explosive diarrhea in her bed while she was taking a nap. She did make it to her colonoscopy and was properly cleaned out. 

08/04/14: The patient was able to have her colonoscopy, but that the physician had to suction a lot of liquid stool from her rectum so they could perform the procedure. They have not yet gotten all of the results of the procedure from their physician, but that the patient did have two polyps removed.  After having all of the explosive diarrhea and loose stools, the patient's bottom is raw. They have been using a desitin product that was recommended by their doctor, and that she is feeling much better.

CONCOMITANT PRODUCTS AND THERAPY DATES

Omeprazole; Valium; Amitriptyline; Acetaminophen; Biotin; Vitamin B12 Energy Sublingual; Vitamin D3; L-Lysine; Omega XL for inflamation</narrativeincludeclinical>
